Justice Jide Falola of the Osun State High Court sitting in Ila-Orangun yesterday sentenced two men to death by hanging for armed robbery. The convicts, Ayodeji Adeleke and Abiodun Oyedunmola, were arraigned on two counts charge of armed robbery and conspiracy. The prosecution counsel from the state Ministry of Justice, Muyiwa Ogunleye, told the court that the convicts committed the offence on April 14, 2016, when they attacked Owonifari Muiydeen at his house in Oke-Ila. Ogunleye added that the convicts also robbed one Mr Bayepade Olubunmi on April 3, 2016, and Afolabi Clement on March 28, 2016. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here They were eventually arrested and arraigned before the court on May 24, 2019. Ogunleye called five witnesses and tendered 11 exhibits, including the confessional statements of convicts, one cartridge ammunition, one gun and two handsets. The counsel to the convicts, Sulaimon Bello, pleaded with the court to be lenient with his clients. Justice Jide Falola said the prosecution counsel proved his case against the defendants beyond reasonable doubt. He consequently found them guilty and sentenced them to death by hanging.  Court sentences two armed robbers to death by hanging 3 sentenced to death for robbery in Osun 2 to die by hanging for murder in Osun